🌍 GFOS — Global Financial Operating System

"One dashboard. Every financial rail on earth."
From SWIFT wire transfers to M-Pesa to Bitcoin — see where money is moving, across all of them, at once.

🔎 What is GFOS?

GFOS is an open-source financial intelligence platform that unifies observation across every layer of the global financial system into a single dashboard. It does not move money — it watches where money moves, across all rail types simultaneously.

🚨 The Problem It Solves

The global financial system moves $190 trillion annually across 4 separate, siloed worlds:

| World | Examples | Current Intelligence |
|---|---|---|
| Banking Rails | SWIFT, ACH, SEPA, Fedwire, CHAPS, CIPS | Bloomberg (expensive, siloed) |
| Remittance Apps | Wise, Western Union, Remitly, WorldRemit | None — completely dark |
| Mobile Money | M-Pesa, MTN MoMo, Wave, Airtel | None — completely dark |
| Crypto Networks | USDC/Solana, USDT/TRON, Stellar, Bitcoin | Chainalysis (crypto-only) |

GFOS collapses all four into one system.

🧩 Core Intelligence Modules

| Module | What It Observes | Status |
|---|---|---|
| Banking Rail Monitor | SWIFT corridors, ACH volumes, wire signals | 🔨 Building |
| Remittance App Tracker | Volume trends, corridor share, fees | 🔨 Building |
| Mobile Money Monitor | Network flows, corridor dominance, seasonal patterns | 🔨 Building |
| Crypto Flow Intelligence | On-chain volume, stablecoin flows, congestion | 🔨 Building |
| FX Signal Engine | Cross-rail FX pressure, spreads, arbitrage | 🔨 Building |
| Congestion Detector | Bottlenecks across all rail types | 🔨 Building |
| Liquidity Heatmap | Global liquidity concentration | 🔨 Building |
| Corridor Intelligence | Dominant rail per corridor | 🔨 Building |
| AI Pattern Engine | Predict rail shifts before they happen | 📋 Planned |
| Regulation Pulse | Policy changes, capital controls | 📋 Planned |
| Unified Dashboard | One screen — every rail, every signal | 📋 Planned |

🚀 Quick Start

git clone https://github.com/your-org/gfos.git
cd gfos
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn backend.api.main:app --reload

Query a corridor
curl "http://localhost:8000/v1/corridors/KE-DE/intelligence"

Compare all rails
curl "http://localhost:8000/v1/corridors/KE-DE/rails/compare"

Global heatmap
curl "http://localhost:8000/v1/heatmap/snapshot"

Which rails are surging?
curl "http://localhost:8000/v1/rails/surging?threshold=0.15"

💻 SDK Usage

Python and TypeScript SDKs are provided, supporting:
- Corridor intelligence (cross-rail dominant flow, volume trends, rail breakdowns)
- Side-by-side rail comparison (volume index, fee index, speed)
- Surging rail detection across all categories
- Banking/crypto/mobile rail signal queries
- Live streaming of all rails via WebSocket

🗺️ Full Rail Coverage

🏦 Banking Rails
SWIFT, SEPA/SEPA Instant, ACH, Fedwire, CHAPS, CIPS, RTGS (80+ countries), IMPS/UPI

💸 Remittance Apps
Wise, Western Union, Remitly, WorldRemit, Sendwave, MoneyGram, Paysend

📱 Mobile Money
M-Pesa, MTN MoMo, Airtel Money, Wave, Orange Money, GCash, bKash, Easypaisa

₿ Crypto Networks
Solana (USDC), TRON (USDT), Stellar (XLM), Ethereum, Bitcoin, Lightning Network

💹 FX Markets
170+ live currency pairs, parallel market divergence signals, spread widening indicators

🏗️ Architecture Stack

Data Sources → Data Collectors (Python) → Streaming Layer (Kafka/Redis)
    → Database Layer (PostgreSQL + Neo4j) → Intelligence Layer
        → API Layer (FastAPI) → Unified Dashboard (Next.js + Mapbox + D3.js)

👥 Who It's For

- Central Banks & Regulators — unified view of capital flows across all rails
- Fintechs & Remittance Operators — corridor monitoring and competitor intelligence
- Impact Investors & Development Finance — emerging market capital flow mapping
- Trade Finance Desks — early cross-border volume shift signals
- Hedge Funds & Macro Analysts — machine-readable remittance leading indicators
- Researchers & Journalists — first open, unified global money flow dataset

